      "body": "**Run 0010 T12 reconcile (r1, session 0008-horizon-T12): PASS \u2014 Stacks 01XJ closed, build green, one blueprint mismatch fixed.**\n\nSupersedes `I-0090` (the r0/01I8 reconcile); this covers the whole run-0010 T12 arc.\n\n- **Verified green + axiom-clean**: `Scheme.Modules.pushforward_isQuasicoherent`, `isLocalizedModule_basicOpen_of_isCompact`, and `isIso_fromTilde\u0393_pullback_fromSpec_of_isLocalizedModule` all `#print axioms` = `propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound`. `lake build AlgebraicJacobian.Picard.QuotScheme` exit 0 (8558 jobs). No stray files; working tree clean.\n- **Sorry counts reconciled**: `QuotScheme.lean` 11 \u2192 10 (across the two sub-rounds: 01I8 then 01XJ, 12 \u2192 10). Cone `AJC.picrep` stays **active** \u2014 headline representability decls remain deep, Mathlib-v4.31-gapped.\n- **Blueprint fix (Ground, this session)**: the `lem:pushforward_isQuasicoherent` node had a malformed header (`\\leanok` before the `[title]`, so the title rendered as body) **and a wrong `\\lean{}` pointer** (`AlgebraicGeometry.pushforward_isQuasicoherent`, a non-existent constant). Corrected to the real FQN `AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.pushforward_isQuasicoherent` so the DAG matches the certified proof. Both were pre-existing stub defects, not from the T12 session; the session correctly rewrote the wrong \"right adjoints preserve quasi-coherence\" sketch to the real MV-localization argument.\n- **Still open**: the helper `pushforward_isQuasicoherent_over_affine` has no blueprint node (content inlined in the 01XJ proof) \u2014 fold into the `I-0087` blueprint pass if strict 1-1 is wanted. `I-0087` (union-merge cluster unblueprinted + dangling `\\cref`s) remains valid; the session repaired only `lem:qcoh_section_localization_basicOpen`.",
